defaultmere 1000 on the previous quarter with male unemployment increasing marginally.  Moreover, such figures understate the extent of the problem
default.
default  For example in her oral evidence Professor Maguire 
defaultdrew attention to the high numbers of workless young women who did not feature in the labour statistics.
default There seems 
defaultto be 
defaultlittle 
defaultshort-term
default 
defaultprospect of sustained improvement. Indeed, the Work Foundation has argued that, since the start of the recession, the UK has experienced the fastest rise in youth unemployment of any of the Group of Eight (G8) countries
default 
